<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bpmn:definitions xmlns:bpmn="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/MODEL"
                  xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
                  xmlns:zeebe="http://camunda.org/schema/zeebe/1.0"
                  xmlns:dc="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DC"
                  xmlns:di="http://www.omg.org/spec/DD/20100524/DI"
                  xmlns:bpmndi="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/20100524/DI"
                  targetNamespace="http://studious-invention/workflows"
                  exporter="Claude" exporterVersion="1.0">

  <bpmn:process id="create-backend-service-simple" name="Create Backend Service (Simple)" isExecutable="true">

    <bpmn:startEvent id="start" name="Service Requested">
      <bpmn:outgoing>flow-start-to-phase1</bpmn:outgoing>
    </bpmn:startEvent>

    <!-- ================================================================
         PHASE 1: INITIALIZE REVIEWS
         Parallel:
           A) Create Threat Model Diagram → Create Application Architecture Review
           B) Create Security Application Review
           C) Setup SonarQube
         ================================================================ -->
    <bpmn:subProcess id="phase-1-initialize-reviews" name="Phase 1: Initialize Reviews">
      <bpmn:incoming>flow-start-to-phase1</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>flow-phase1-to-phase2</bpmn:outgoing>

      <bpmn:startEvent id="phase1-start">
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-p1-start-to-fork</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:startEvent>

      <bpmn:parallelGateway id="p1-fork">
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-p1-start-to-fork</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-p1-fork-to-threat-model</bpmn:outgoing>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-p1-fork-to-security-review</bpmn:outgoing>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-p1-fork-to-sonarqube</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:parallelGateway>

      <bpmn:userTask id="create-threat-model" name="Create Threat Model Diagram">
        <bpmn:documentation>## Threat Model

Document the trust boundaries and data flows for the new service using
the **STRIDE** methodology.

**Tooling:** OWASP Threat Dragon or the team draw.io template stored in
the platform Confluence space.

Outputs required before marking complete:
- A diagram exported as `.png` attached to this task
- A completed STRIDE matrix (even if all cells are N/A)</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="description" value="Create a STRIDE threat model diagram and matrix; attach PNG export and completed matrix before completing." />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-p1-fork-to-threat-model</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-threat-model-to-arch-review</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>

      <bpmn:userTask id="create-arch-review" name="Create Application Architecture Review">
        <bpmn:documentation>## Architecture Review Board

Present the threat model output to the Architecture Review Board (ARB)
for sign-off.

**Minimum attendees:**
- 1 platform engineer
- 1 security engineer
- The service's tech lead

The ARB decision and any conditions must be recorded as a comment on
this task before it is completed.</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="description" value="Present threat model to ARB; minimum attendees are platform engineer, security engineer, and tech lead." />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-threat-model-to-arch-review</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-arch-review-to-p1-join</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>

      <bpmn:userTask id="create-security-app-review" name="Create Security Application Review">
        <bpmn:documentation>## Security Application Review

The security team performs a manual review of the application design
against the **OWASP ASVS Level 2** checklist.

Key areas covered:
- Authentication and session management
- Access control model
- Input validation and output encoding
- Secrets and cryptographic practices

All findings are recorded in the security tracker and linked to this
task before it is marked complete.</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="description" value="Security team reviews the design against OWASP ASVS Level 2; all findings must be tracked before completing." />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-p1-fork-to-security-review</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-security-review-to-p1-join</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>

      <bpmn:userTask id="setup-sonarqube" name="Setup SonarQube">
        <bpmn:documentation>## SonarQube Configuration

Adds the service to the shared SonarQube instance and configures the
default quality profile for the project language.

> **Note:** This workflow uses the internal SonarQube instance. For
> new services consider the cloud-native SonarCloud path in the
> `create-backend-api` workflow instead.

The project token must be stored in Vault at
`secret/ci/{{ serviceId }}/sonarqube`.</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="description" value="Adds the service to internal SonarQube with the default quality profile; stores project token in Vault." />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-p1-fork-to-sonarqube</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-sonarqube-to-p1-join</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>

      <bpmn:parallelGateway id="p1-join">
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-arch-review-to-p1-join</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-security-review-to-p1-join</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-sonarqube-to-p1-join</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-p1-join-to-phase1-end</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:parallelGateway>

      <bpmn:endEvent id="phase1-end">
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-p1-join-to-phase1-end</bpmn:incoming>
      </bpmn:endEvent>

      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-p1-start-to-fork"           sourceRef="phase1-start"              targetRef="p1-fork" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-p1-fork-to-threat-model"    sourceRef="p1-fork"                   targetRef="create-threat-model" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-p1-fork-to-security-review" sourceRef="p1-fork"                   targetRef="create-security-app-review" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-p1-fork-to-sonarqube"       sourceRef="p1-fork"                   targetRef="setup-sonarqube" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-threat-model-to-arch-review" sourceRef="create-threat-model"      targetRef="create-arch-review" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-arch-review-to-p1-join"     sourceRef="create-arch-review"        targetRef="p1-join" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-security-review-to-p1-join" sourceRef="create-security-app-review" targetRef="p1-join" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-sonarqube-to-p1-join"       sourceRef="setup-sonarqube"           targetRef="p1-join" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-p1-join-to-phase1-end"      sourceRef="p1-join"                   targetRef="phase1-end" />
    </bpmn:subProcess>

    <!-- ================================================================
         PHASE 2: BUILD APPLICATION
         Parallel:
           A) Build Application
           B) Write E2E Tests
           C) Write Unit Tests
         ================================================================ -->
    <bpmn:subProcess id="phase-2-build-application" name="Phase 2: Build Application">
      <bpmn:incoming>flow-phase1-to-phase2</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>flow-phase2-to-phase3</bpmn:outgoing>

      <bpmn:startEvent id="phase2-start">
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-p2-start-to-fork</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:startEvent>

      <bpmn:parallelGateway id="p2-fork">
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-p2-start-to-fork</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-p2-fork-to-build</bpmn:outgoing>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-p2-fork-to-e2e</bpmn:outgoing>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-p2-fork-to-unit</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:parallelGateway>

      <bpmn:userTask id="build-application" name="Build Application">
        <bpmn:documentation>## Application Build

Developer implements the service skeleton based on the architecture
review output from Phase 1.

**Must pass before completing:**
- `ruff check .` with zero violations
- `mypy --strict` with no suppressions added beyond the baseline
- All pre-commit hooks green on the feature branch
- At least one passing integration test against a local Docker stack</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="description" value="Implement service skeleton; must pass ruff, mypy strict, pre-commit hooks, and one integration test before completing." />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-p2-fork-to-build</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-build-to-p2-join</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>

      <bpmn:userTask id="write-e2e-tests" name="Write E2E Tests">
        <bpmn:documentation>## E2E Test Suite

Write end-to-end tests covering the happy path and at least one
negative-path scenario per public endpoint.

Tests live under `tests/e2e/` and are tagged `@smoke` for the CD
post-deploy gate.

Run locally with:
```bash
uv run pytest tests/e2e/ -m smoke --base-url http://localhost:8000
```</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="description" value="E2E tests covering happy and negative paths per endpoint; tagged @smoke for CD gate, run against a local stack." />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-p2-fork-to-e2e</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-e2e-to-p2-join</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>

      <bpmn:userTask id="write-unit-tests" name="Write Unit Tests">
        <bpmn:documentation>## Unit Test Coverage

Target: **≥ 80 %** line coverage on all non-generated modules.

Use `pytest-mock` for mocking external dependencies and avoid any
real network or filesystem calls in unit tests.

```bash
uv run pytest tests/unit/ --cov=src --cov-fail-under=80
```

Coverage reports are uploaded to SonarQube automatically by CI.</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="description" value="Write unit tests targeting 80%+ coverage with pytest-mock; no real I/O calls; CI uploads results to SonarQube." />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-p2-fork-to-unit</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-unit-to-p2-join</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>

      <bpmn:parallelGateway id="p2-join">
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-build-to-p2-join</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-e2e-to-p2-join</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-unit-to-p2-join</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-p2-join-to-phase2-end</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:parallelGateway>

      <bpmn:endEvent id="phase2-end">
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-p2-join-to-phase2-end</bpmn:incoming>
      </bpmn:endEvent>

      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-p2-start-to-fork"     sourceRef="phase2-start"      targetRef="p2-fork" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-p2-fork-to-build"     sourceRef="p2-fork"           targetRef="build-application" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-p2-fork-to-e2e"       sourceRef="p2-fork"           targetRef="write-e2e-tests" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-p2-fork-to-unit"      sourceRef="p2-fork"           targetRef="write-unit-tests" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-build-to-p2-join"     sourceRef="build-application" targetRef="p2-join" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-e2e-to-p2-join"       sourceRef="write-e2e-tests"   targetRef="p2-join" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-unit-to-p2-join"      sourceRef="write-unit-tests"  targetRef="p2-join" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-p2-join-to-phase2-end" sourceRef="p2-join"          targetRef="phase2-end" />
    </bpmn:subProcess>

    <!-- ================================================================
         PHASE 3: COMPLETE APPLICATION
         Parallel:
           A) Resolve Security Application Review Findings
           B) Resolve SonarQube Findings
           C) Deploy to Dev
         ================================================================ -->
    <bpmn:subProcess id="phase-3-complete-application" name="Phase 3: Complete Application">
      <bpmn:incoming>flow-phase2-to-phase3</bpmn:incoming>
      <bpmn:outgoing>flow-phase3-to-end</bpmn:outgoing>

      <bpmn:startEvent id="phase3-start">
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-p3-start-to-fork</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:startEvent>

      <bpmn:parallelGateway id="p3-fork">
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-p3-start-to-fork</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-p3-fork-to-resolve-security</bpmn:outgoing>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-p3-fork-to-resolve-sonarqube</bpmn:outgoing>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-p3-fork-to-deploy-dev</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:parallelGateway>

      <bpmn:userTask id="resolve-security-findings" name="Resolve Security Application Review Findings">
        <bpmn:documentation>## Remediate Security Findings

Address all **high** and **critical** findings raised during the security
application review in Phase 1.

Each finding must be linked to a resolved Jira ticket before this task
is completed. Accepted dispositions:

- **Fixed** — code change merged and verified
- **Mitigated** — compensating control documented
- **Accepted** — risk accepted by the CISO in writing</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="description" value="Resolve all high/critical security findings; each needs a Jira ticket with fixed, mitigated, or CISO-accepted disposition." />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-p3-fork-to-resolve-security</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-resolve-security-to-p3-join</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>

      <bpmn:userTask id="resolve-sonarqube-findings" name="Resolve SonarQube Findings">
        <bpmn:documentation>## SonarQube Remediation

Resolve all issues that breach the quality gate:

- **Blocker** issues — must be fixed, no exceptions
- **Critical** issues — must be fixed or formally suppressed
- **Coverage &lt; 80 %** — add tests until the threshold is met

Issues marked _Won't Fix_ require a tech-lead comment explaining the
business justification.</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="description" value="Resolve SonarQube blockers and criticals and reach 80% coverage; Won't Fix decisions require tech-lead justification." />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-p3-fork-to-resolve-sonarqube</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-resolve-sonarqube-to-p3-join</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>

      <bpmn:userTask id="deploy-to-dev" name="Deploy to Dev">
        <bpmn:documentation>## Dev Environment Deploy

Deploys the first working build to the shared `dev` environment using
the platform CI job.

Smoke tests run automatically post-deploy and results are posted to the
`#deployments` Slack channel.

> The `dev` environment is **shared** — coordinate with other teams
> before deploying if you expect destructive schema migrations.</bpmn:documentation>
        <bpmn:extensionElements>
          <zeebe:properties>
            <zeebe:property name="description" value="Deploys to the shared dev environment; smoke tests run automatically and post results to #deployments Slack." />
          </zeebe:properties>
        </bpmn:extensionElements>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-p3-fork-to-deploy-dev</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-deploy-dev-to-p3-join</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:userTask>

      <bpmn:parallelGateway id="p3-join">
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-resolve-security-to-p3-join</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-resolve-sonarqube-to-p3-join</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-deploy-dev-to-p3-join</bpmn:incoming>
        <bpmn:outgoing>flow-p3-join-to-phase3-end</bpmn:outgoing>
      </bpmn:parallelGateway>

      <bpmn:endEvent id="phase3-end">
        <bpmn:incoming>flow-p3-join-to-phase3-end</bpmn:incoming>
      </bpmn:endEvent>

      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-p3-start-to-fork"            sourceRef="phase3-start"               targetRef="p3-fork" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-p3-fork-to-resolve-security"  sourceRef="p3-fork"                   targetRef="resolve-security-findings" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-p3-fork-to-resolve-sonarqube" sourceRef="p3-fork"                   targetRef="resolve-sonarqube-findings" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-p3-fork-to-deploy-dev"        sourceRef="p3-fork"                   targetRef="deploy-to-dev" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-resolve-security-to-p3-join"  sourceRef="resolve-security-findings" targetRef="p3-join" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-resolve-sonarqube-to-p3-join" sourceRef="resolve-sonarqube-findings" targetRef="p3-join" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-deploy-dev-to-p3-join"        sourceRef="deploy-to-dev"             targetRef="p3-join" />
      <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-p3-join-to-phase3-end"        sourceRef="p3-join"                   targetRef="phase3-end" />
    </bpmn:subProcess>

    <bpmn:endEvent id="end" name="Service Complete">
      <bpmn:incoming>flow-phase3-to-end</bpmn:incoming>
    </bpmn:endEvent>

    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-start-to-phase1"  sourceRef="start"                        targetRef="phase-1-initialize-reviews" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-phase1-to-phase2" sourceRef="phase-1-initialize-reviews"   targetRef="phase-2-build-application" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-phase2-to-phase3" sourceRef="phase-2-build-application"    targetRef="phase-3-complete-application" />
    <bpmn:sequenceFlow id="flow-phase3-to-end"    sourceRef="phase-3-complete-application" targetRef="end" />

  </bpmn:process>

  <!-- ================================================================
       DIAGRAM INTERCHANGE
       Main flow at y=410. Subprocess rows: top=180, mid=410, bot=640.
       All coordinates are absolute.
       ================================================================ -->
  <bpmndi:BPMNDiagram id="BPMNDiagram_1">
    <bpmndi:BPMNPlane id="BPMNPlane_1" bpmnElement="create-backend-service-simple">

      <!-- ── TOP-LEVEL ELEMENTS ── -->
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="start_di" bpmnElement="start">
        <dc:Bounds x="152" y="392" width="36" height="36" />
        <bpmndi:BPMNLabel><dc:Bounds x="128" y="435" width="85" height="14" /></bpmndi:BPMNLabel>
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>

      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="phase-1-initialize-reviews_di" bpmnElement="phase-1-initialize-reviews" isExpanded="true">
        <dc:Bounds x="230" y="60" width="1000" height="700" />
        <bpmndi:BPMNLabel />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>

      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="phase-2-build-application_di" bpmnElement="phase-2-build-application" isExpanded="true">
        <dc:Bounds x="1290" y="160" width="560" height="500" />
        <bpmndi:BPMNLabel />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>

      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="phase-3-complete-application_di" bpmnElement="phase-3-complete-application" isExpanded="true">
        <dc:Bounds x="1910" y="60" width="700" height="700" />
        <bpmndi:BPMNLabel />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>

      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="end_di" bpmnElement="end">
        <dc:Bounds x="2672" y="392" width="36" height="36" />
        <bpmndi:BPMNLabel><dc:Bounds x="2648" y="435" width="85" height="14" /></bpmndi:BPMNLabel>
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>

      <!-- top-level sequence flows -->
      <bpmndi:BPMNEdge id="flow-start-to-phase1_di" bpmnElement="flow-start-to-phase1">
        <di:waypoint x="188" y="410" /><di:waypoint x="230" y="410" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNEdge>
      <bpmndi:BPMNEdge id="flow-phase1-to-phase2_di" bpmnElement="flow-phase1-to-phase2">
        <di:waypoint x="1230" y="410" /><di:waypoint x="1290" y="410" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNEdge>
      <bpmndi:BPMNEdge id="flow-phase2-to-phase3_di" bpmnElement="flow-phase2-to-phase3">
        <di:waypoint x="1850" y="410" /><di:waypoint x="1910" y="410" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNEdge>
      <bpmndi:BPMNEdge id="flow-phase3-to-end_di" bpmnElement="flow-phase3-to-end">
        <di:waypoint x="2610" y="410" /><di:waypoint x="2672" y="410" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNEdge>

      <!-- ── PHASE 1 INTERNAL ──
           subprocess: x=230 y=60 w=1000 h=700  (right edge x=1230)
           branch rows: top y=180, mid y=410, bot y=640
      -->
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="phase1-start_di" bpmnElement="phase1-start">
        <dc:Bounds x="272" y="392" width="36" height="36" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="p1-fork_di" bpmnElement="p1-fork">
        <dc:Bounds x="355" y="385" width="50" height="50" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="create-threat-model_di" bpmnElement="create-threat-model">
        <dc:Bounds x="450" y="140" width="100" height="80" />
        <bpmndi:BPMNLabel />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="create-arch-review_di" bpmnElement="create-arch-review">
        <dc:Bounds x="610" y="140" width="100" height="80" />
        <bpmndi:BPMNLabel />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="create-security-app-review_di" bpmnElement="create-security-app-review">
        <dc:Bounds x="450" y="370" width="100" height="80" />
        <bpmndi:BPMNLabel />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="setup-sonarqube_di" bpmnElement="setup-sonarqube">
        <dc:Bounds x="450" y="600" width="100" height="80" />
        <bpmndi:BPMNLabel />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="p1-join_di" bpmnElement="p1-join">
        <dc:Bounds x="785" y="385" width="50" height="50" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>
      <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="phase1-end_di" bpmnElement="phase1-end">
        <dc:Bounds x="882" y="392" width="36" height="36" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>

      <bpmndi:BPMNEdge id="flow-p1-start-to-fork_di" bpmnElement="flow-p1-start-to-fork">
        <di:waypoint x="308" y="410" /><di:waypoint x="355" y="410" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNEdge>
      <bpmndi:BPMNEdge id="flow-p1-fork-to-threat-model_di" bpmnElement="flow-p1-fork-to-threat-model">
        <di:waypoint x="380" y="385" /><di:waypoint x="380" y="180" /><di:waypoint x="450" y="180" />
      </bpmndi:BPMNEdge>
